parameters: \n<\n[1]>You!\.\. Big!\.\. Ugly!\.\. Move from the door!\.\. I have to reach the Hole!!
\n<\n[1]>What's with this guy?\.\. I don't like it one bit...
Neneko heaves,\. groaning and meowing as she rolls onto her side.\.\.
A cool breeze washes over the fallen cat.\.\. Was she...\.\.\. outside?\.\.
A glance around tells her that she's on...\.\.\. some kind of cliff.\.\. No,\. this...\.\.\. she must be over the Hole,\. which means that metal platform there is...\.\.\. the Lift!\.\.
She tries to sit up,\. before cursing and dropping back to the cold floor,\. hand on her stomach.\.\.
Neneko darts her head up,\. grimacing.\.\.
Emma is there,\. walking forward confidently,\. a sway to her hips and with even steps,\. stepping over a broken piece of wood.\.\.
She doesn't look strained at all,\. completely calm and uncaring of the carnage she'd just wrought with a single attack.\.\.
Even Neneko couldn't help but begin to shake.\.\.
\n<Emma>I'm a bit impressed,\. honestly.\.\. I was expecting to shatter your spine,\. or at least gore an organ or two,\. but you just look a bit roughed up at worst.\.\.
\n<Emma>How do you do it?\.\. Being a Cat give you nine lives?\.\. How many did that hit kill,\. then?\.\.
She turns her head up to the shattered exit gate.\.\.
\n<Emma>Damn...\.\.\. that right there?\.\. That's why I don't like going all out.\.\. It's way too much effort,\. and then there's always collateral damage...\.\.\.
She groans,\. looking even more exhausted,\. bringing a hand up to rub her eyes.\.\.
n<Emma>Explaining this is going to be a huge headache.\.\. I'll be lucky if I can even close my eyes by tonight,\. let alone sleep...\.\.\.
\n<Emma>Ugh...\.\.\. let's just get all this over with.\.\. Maybe if I clean up fast they'll harass me a bit less...\.\.\.
Emma raises her mace,\. stepping forward.\.\.
\n<Emma>Don't get up again.\.\. I'm making this quick.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>You...\.\.\. *cough...\.\.\.* you haven't won yet,\. dammit...\.\.\. \BST[3]I'm too close...\.\.\. I'm going down that Hole...!\.\.
\n<Emma>What's even down there for you?\.\. I don't get why people are always so obsessed with this place.\.\.
\n<Emma>For me,\. it's just an annoying job that keeps me up at night.\.\.
\n<Emma>Whatever.\.\. You can talk as big a game as you want for someone with their stomach caved in.\.\. I don't care about your reasons.\.\.
Emma walks forward,\. ready to strike.\.\.
Considering the speed and power of the last one,\. Neneko finds herself not feeling particularly optimistic about her chances.\.\. Especially with the Hole behind her.\.\.
If she gets launched like before here...\.\.\. well,\. she'd definitely travel down like she intended,\. but surviving the trip...\.\.\.
A glow begins to come from the bottom of Neneko's vision.\.\.
Neneko looks down,\. seeing the source of the glow,\. coming from around her neck.\.\.
\n<Anzu>The Amon Crystal?\.\. Is it...\.\.\. reacting to something?\.\. Now?\.\.
From below,\. an intense bright flash escapes the Hole,\. a loud clap of thunder following close behind,\. almost enough to hurt Neneko's ears.\.\.
A beam of light,\. almost like lightning arcs through the sky,\. the girls on the lift staring up in shock...\.\.\.
And then the light comes downward,\. aimed straight for the lift.\.\.
Emma leaps out of the way,\. back to the safety of the building,\. but...\.\.\.
All Neneko sees is white,\. and all she feels is a searing burning sensation...\.\.\.
And then the feeling of the ground collapsing underneath her,\. the twisting of metal echoing in her ears as a numbness takes hold.\.\.
The Lift took a direct hit from that strange magical lightning along with her,\. and unlike her,\. it apparently didn't survive the blast.\.\.
But the Lift was the least of her concerns,\. as she found herself falling into the abyss below,\. her vision fading as exhaustion and pain took hold...\.\.\.
\n<Emma>Shit...\.\.\. this is really bad...\.\.\. I'm going to get an earful for this entire mess for sure...\.\.\.
